My distance ed institution is some way to go yet with a centralised notebook service, but we do currently have a course running with:

- ~500 students working with individual notebook servers running in VMs on their own computers;
- ~20 tutors with an allocation of about ~25 students each;
- 3 pieces of assessed work: in the first two, each assessment is set using separate questions spread across ~3 notebooks per assessment; the last assessment is a data investigation report.

I'm looking to find a way of using nbgrader to set and manually mark / comment on notebook based assessments.

Ideally, I'd like a process something along the lines of:

- central academic team create assessment notebook(s) for manual grading and with marking guide annoations; 
- central academic team export notebook files stripped of marking guide notes that can be published as static files on VLE and downloaded by students from there; annotated notebooks with marking guidance are exported for download by markers from tutor area of VLE.
- student to enter an ID number and name into their notebook assessed notebooks, run the notebooks, zip them and then submit the zip file as an attachment through our legacy online assessment handling tools;
- tutor/markers to use our legacy assessment handling tool to download zip files containing submissions from each of their students; (we don't control the zip structure of the outer layer which is of the form courseCode/assignmentCode/tutorID/region/studentID)
- markers point grading tool at downloaded student files and load them into grading tool showing assignment/student listing; ideally, markers would also be able 
- markers manually mark and comment on notebook assignments;
- marked/annotated notebooks are pushed back into our legacy marking tool directory structure and returned using legacy tools;
- students collect annotated notebooks from legacy system and inspect notebooks. Marker comments should be clearly highlighted.

(We might be able to fudge the return handler by building a custom return handler that bundles files in the way the legacy online assignment handling tool expects.)

What I'm not sure is how to tease out / configure just the bits of nbgrader we need to make to support this workflow wherever we can?

Markers are also running their own VMs on their own hardware.

